3.
Eligibility for empanelment as mediator.-The following persons shall be eligible to be empanelled with a
Mediation Cell-
(i)
retired Judges of Supreme Court of India;
(ii)
retired Judges of the High Courts;
(iii)
retired Members of a Consumer Commission;
(iv)
retired District and Session Judges, retired Additional District and Session Judges or other retired
Members of the Higher Judicial Services of a State;
(v)
retired Judicial officers, having experience of not less    than ten years;
(vi)
an advocate with a minimum experience of ten years at Bar;
(vii)
the mediators empanelled with the Mediation Cell of the Supreme Court of India, High Court or a
District Court;
(viii)
a person having experience of at least five years in mediation or conciliation;
(ix)
experts or other professionals with at least fifteen years’ experience or retired senior bureaucrats or
retired executives.
